Package: corpuscomp
Type: Package
Title: STATS 290 Project: Analyzing Corpus Data at the Character Level 
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Kate", "Li", email = "kateli@stanford.edu", 
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
    person("Sang", "Truong", 
           role = c("ctb", "med"))
    )
Description: This package takes in corpus-level data: in particular, it develops analytical
  frameworks to help users analyze trends in character representation for the constituent documents
  within a corpus. Given a preprocessed set of documents (e.g., parses generated by the NLP pipeline,
  "BookNLP"), it helps users wrangle, visualize and document how characters are characterized within 
  their corpus of literary texts. 
